cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.IT. 

This paper discusses the relative expressiveness of Bayesian and neural networks, which are both commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also touches on systems and control theory (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT) in its discussion of the testing operator.
